parameters: [Mysterious Woman] I thought someone had broken the barrier...

[Mysterious Woman] You don't seem to have a single hair on your body,
just a little girl.
[Anastasia] You seem to be quite uncouth.
[Anastasia] Are you the culprit who kidnapped the academy students?

[Mysterious Woman: How dare you, a little girl, speak so insolently to
the great sorceress Gizelmina-sama.

[Gizelmina] I was planning to let you live after draining your
magical power, you know.

[Anastasia] Why did you go through the trouble of setting up such a
large barrier and gathering magic power? What were you trying to
accomplish?
[Gizelmina] I don't have the obligation to tell you, but...
[Gizelmina] Such a beautiful and lovely face...

[Gizelmina] You called me a little girl, but... rather, that weak
body that hasn't fully grown as a woman...

[Gizelmina] And yet, you have such an insolent and aggressive
attitude...

[Gizelmina] I've taken a liking to you, so I'll tell you something
special.
[Anastasia] Let's retract what I said earlier.

[Anastasia] It's not that you lack refinement, but your very nature
seems quite base.

[Anastasia] Even if you don't tell me, well, I can imagine it to some
extent.

[Gizelmina] Well, please listen without saying that. If you can
imagine it, I'll keep it brief.
[Anastasia] It's quite an interesting story, but...

[Anastasia] I see... It's a bit vague, but I can start to see the
reason why you were abducting students from the academy.
[Gizelmina] But please listen a little more.

[Gizelmina] Sorcery is a field of study created to understand the
very laws of physics.

[Gizelmina] I can't change chemical changes at the atomic and
molecular level, such as freezing water or burning oxygen.
[Gizelmina] But even beyond those laws of physics...

[Gizelmina] If we were to make magic, the very laws of nature,
visible, wouldn't it be something akin to a god?

[Anastasia] Indeed, if it were possible to materialize the laws of
nature, it could be said to be an existence akin to a god.

[Anastasia] It's probably a story that won't become a reality for
hundreds of years.

[Gizelmina] But you know, there are things within the laws of nature
that can be manipulated and controlled by physical phenomena such as
sound, heat, and smell, and can be materialized and manipulated to an
infinite extent.

[Gizelmina] I was only studying magic that interferes with human
emotions.

[Gizelmina] But, you know, I was having trouble gathering magic power
more than I thought.

[Anastasia] Hehe, I don't think it's a research that can earn much
respect.
[Anastasia] Rather, I despised her even more.
[Anastasia] In any case, since it is research that harms people,
[Anastasia] Hehe, there's no choice but for you to disappear.

[Gizelmina] I will drain your magic power and make sure you can't

[Anastasia] Hehe, you were quite a formidable opponent, weren't you?
[Anastasia] However, let's bring this battle to an end soon.
[Gizelmina] Don't be in such a hurry.
[Gizelmina] I still have a trump card up my sleeve.
[Gizelmina] Can you still laugh like that? Ahhhhh!!

[Anastasia] Because we're fighting against an unknown enemy...
[Anastasia] It is only natural to be prepared in advance.
[Anastasia] This time, let's truly put an end to it.

[Gizelmina] I wonder if we really managed to deal with magic using

[Gizelmina] If that item is the real deal...
[Gizelmina] We might have been able to prevent it...
[Gizelmina] I've made it so you can't use your troublesome sorcery.

[Gizelmina] I've made it so you can enlarge
